article.description: — DJ Davis scored 25 points as UC Irvine beat New Mexico State 85-68 in the Las Vegas Classic on Saturday.
article.headline: Davis scores 25, leads UC Irvine past New Mexico State 85-68
article.linkText: Davis scores 25, leads UC Irvine past New Mexico State 85-68
article.story: LAS VEGAS -- — DJ Davis scored 25 points as UC Irvine beat New Mexico State 85-68 in the Las Vegas Classic on Saturday. Davis was 8 of 15 shooting, including 5 for 7 from distance, and went 4 for 5 from the foul line for the Anteaters (6-1). Dawson Baker hit three 3-pointers and scored 19. Justin Hohn added 16 points on 5-of-7 shooting. The Aggies (2-2) were led in scoring by Anthony Roy with 20. DaJuan Gordon added 14 points and nine rebounds, while Xavier Pinson scored 10. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
